The generic, non-binary, install for a posix system is done
using the command

      python3 setup.py install --prefix=<prefix>

You will need a working gcc toolchain, python3 (including headers and
libraries), PyGObject (gi.repository) with GTK3, and SDL/SDL_mixer
development libraries for the sound extension.

PyTraffic requires:
  - Python 3
  - GTK 3 with Python bindings (PyGObject / python3-gi)
  - SDL and SDL_mixer (for the _sdl_mixer C extension)
  - GCC toolchain (to build C extensions)

The default prefix is /usr/local. If you use a standard prefix such
as /usr or /usr/local then a menu item will be created for pytraffic.
Otherwise issue the command

     <prefix>/bin/pytraffic

to play.

For other installation methods see doc/readme.htm.
